  "features": [
    {
      "name": "Spellcasting",
      "html description": "<p>As a wizard, you gain the ability to cast spells. Your spellbook contains the spells you know, and you prepare a list of wizard spells to cast.</p>\n<h5>Cantrips</h5>\n<p>At 1st level, you know three cantrips of your choice from the wizard spell list.</p>\n<h5>Spell Slots</h5>\n<p>The Wizard table shows how many spell slots you have. You regain all expended spell slots when you finish a long rest.</p>\n<h5>Preparing and Casting Spells</h5>\n<p>You prepare a list of wizard spells from your spellbook each day.</p>\n<h5>Spellcasting Ability</h5>\n<p>Intelligence is your spellcasting ability for wizard spells.</p>\n<h5>Ritual Casting</h5>\n<p>You can cast a wizard spell as a ritual if it has the ritual tag and you have the spell in your spellbook.</p>\n<h5>Spellcasting Focus</h5>\n<p>You can use an arcane focus as a spellcasting focus for your wizard spells.</p>\n<h5>Learning Spells of 1st Level and Higher</h5>\n<p>Each time you gain a wizard level, you can add two wizard spells to your spellbook.</p>"
    },
    {
      "name": "Arcane Recovery",
      "html description": "<p>Once per day when you finish a short rest, you can recover expended spell slots (see the class feature for the details and limits).</p>"
    },
    {
      "name": "Arcane Tradition",
      "html description": "<p>When you reach 2nd level, you choose an Arcane Tradition, granting features at 2nd level and again at 6th, 10th, and 14th level.</p>"
    },
    {
      "name": "Cantrip Formulas (Optional)",
      "html description": "<p>At 3rd level, you can replace one wizard cantrip you know with another cantrip from the wizard spell list when you finish a long rest (optional feature).</p>"
    },
    {
      "name": "Ability Score Improvement",
      "html description": "<p>At 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase ability scores as normal.</p>"
    },
    {
      "name": "Spell Mastery",
      "html description": "<p>At 18th level, you can cast one chosen 1st-level wizard spell and one chosen 2nd-level wizard spell at will when prepared (see feature for details, and you can swap them after extended study).</p>"
    },
    {
      "name": "Signature Spells",
      "html description": "<p>At 20th level, choose two 3rd-level wizard spells in your spellbook as signature spells. You always have them prepared, and you can cast each once at 3rd level without expending a spell slot per short/long rest.</p>"
    }
  ]
